 :tx/rationale "PRINCIPLE (should become INV-CONCURRENCY-001): For every mutable artifact in .braid/, there must exist exactly ONE writer at any time. This session's entire investigation reduces to ONE insight: store.bin was a shared mutable cache written by multiple overlapping LiveStores. Every bug we found (dead mtime check, poisoned fingerprint, stale overwrite) is a CONSEQUENCE of violating the single-writer property. The fix restores it: daemon is the single writer for mutable state (store.bin/checkpoint.bin). CLI is stateless. .edn files are immutable (C1). WAL is append-only (single daemon process). This principle PREVENTS future bugs of the same class. Any new mutable artifact in .braid/ must identify its single writer, or it will eventually develop the same cache coherence bugs."
